    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>This is currently not possible with the official API. This question is similar to <a href=\"https://github.com/mapstruct/mapstruct/issues/1427\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">mapstruct/mapstruct#1427</a>.</p>\n\n<p>However, there are 2 options that you can try to make it work.</p>\n\n<hr>\n\n<h3>Option 1 (annotate Mapper)</h3>\n\n<p>You can try to annotate <code>MyMapper</code> with the <code>@Profile</code> annotation, I am not sure whether Spring searches up the inheritance tree and in interface or not</p>\n\n<hr>\n\n<h3>Option 2 (use internal API)</h3>\n\n<p>MapStruct has the <a href=\"https://github.com/mapstruct/mapstruct/blob/master/processor/src/main/java/org/mapstruct/ap/internal/processor/ModelElementProcessor.java\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>ModelElementProcessor</code></a> that it used to add the <code>@Component</code> annotation. The one for Spring is <a href=\"https://github.com/mapstruct/mapstruct/blob/master/processor/src/main/java/org/mapstruct/ap/internal/processor/SpringComponentProcessor.java\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>SpringComponentModelElementProcessor</code></a>.</p>\n\n<p>You can provide your own <code>componentModel</code> (<code>spring-dev</code> for example) that would add the <code>@Profile</code> annotation to the generated mapper.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 158974,
      "reputation" : 472,
      "user_id" : 377971,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/0b10f6c2a3cbcec394422bfa0177245c?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Beholder",
